WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.379 --> 00:00:02.234
Narrator: When most people
buy a house they need

00:00:02.234 --> 00:00:05.889
to borrow money for some part of
the purchase price of the house.

00:00:05.889 --> 00:00:08.882
Let's say that we have
a house right over here

00:00:08.882 --> 00:00:14.194
and the purchase price is $200,000,

00:00:14.194 --> 00:00:18.600
and I want to buy this house,
and I've saved up $40,000.

00:00:18.600 --> 00:00:23.964
I have saved up $40,000,
so this is my savings,

00:00:23.964 --> 00:00:27.253
so I will use this as a down payment,

00:00:27.253 --> 00:00:29.749
but I still need to borrow the rest

00:00:29.749 --> 00:00:32.461
of the money in order to get to $200,000.

00:00:32.461 --> 00:00:43.670
I'm going to have to get the
balance, the $160,000 as a loan.

00:00:43.670 --> 00:00:45.293
The type of loan that
people that people will get,

00:00:45.293 --> 00:00:49.445
or that they usually get to buy
a house is called a mortgage.

00:00:49.445 --> 00:00:52.946
Mortgage. A mortgage is really just a loan

00:00:52.946 --> 00:00:55.992
where if you don't pay the loan off,

00:00:55.992 --> 00:01:00.069
the person that you borrowed
the money from gets the house.

00:01:00.069 --> 00:01:02.860
Another way to think
about it is it's a loan

00:01:02.860 --> 00:01:06.968
that's secured by the house
until you pay off the loan.

00:01:06.968 --> 00:01:08.863
When you pay off the loan
it is your house to keep,

00:01:08.863 --> 00:01:10.970
but at any point if you don't pay it,

00:01:10.970 --> 00:01:12.643
the bank could come and take the house,

00:01:12.643 --> 00:01:14.657
and that is called a foreclosure.

00:01:14.657 --> 00:01:16.787
Now, what I want to focus on in this video

00:01:16.787 --> 00:01:19.629
is the types of mortgage
loans you will typically see,

00:01:19.629 --> 00:01:21.838
and give you at least the beginning

00:01:21.838 --> 00:01:24.467
of an understanding of how to understand

00:01:24.467 --> 00:01:27.092
what these different types of loans mean.

00:01:27.092 --> 00:01:29.562
In all of these scenarios,
let's just assume

00:01:29.562 --> 00:01:33.331
that I'm in the market to borrow $160,000

00:01:33.331 --> 00:01:35.492
for this house I'm about to buy.

00:01:35.492 --> 00:01:39.066
If you look at any
financial website or any

00:01:39.066 --> 00:01:41.227
of the major search-web portals,

00:01:41.227 --> 00:01:43.620
they'll give you quotes
for mortgage rates.

00:01:43.620 --> 00:01:44.965
You'll see something like this.

00:01:44.965 --> 00:01:46.263
I made these numbers really simple.

00:01:46.263 --> 00:01:50.275
Normally, you'll have some decimals here;
5.25%, 4.18%.

00:01:50.275 --> 00:01:55.132
I made these numbers a little bit
simpler just to make them simpler.

00:01:55.132 --> 00:01:57.685
These are the typical types
of mortgage you will see,

00:01:57.685 --> 00:01:59.145
but if you contact mortgage
broker they will have

00:01:59.145 --> 00:02:01.353
many, many more types, more exotic types;

00:02:01.353 --> 00:02:02.745
but these are the most common

00:02:02.745 --> 00:02:04.352
and this is what we'll
cover in this video.

00:02:04.352 --> 00:02:06.043
Hopefully they'll give you a sense

00:02:06.043 --> 00:02:08.127
of what the other types
of mortgage is like.

00:02:08.127 --> 00:02:12.069
A 30 year fixed mortgage
means that your payment

00:02:12.069 --> 00:02:15.117
and your interest rate
are fixed over 30 years,

00:02:15.117 --> 00:02:19.996
and over the course of those 30
years you will pay off your loan.

00:02:19.996 --> 00:02:24.227
In this situation, this is a 30 ...

