00:05:31.256 --> 00:05:35.373
This will happen over 30
years; this is a 30 year term.

00:05:35.373 --> 00:05:38.782
A 15 year fixed is the same exact idea,

00:05:38.782 --> 00:05:44.824
except instead of it taking 30 years

00:05:44.824 --> 00:05:48.335
to pay off the loan, you're
going to do it over 15 years.

00:05:48.335 --> 00:05:50.422
Instead of it being 360 months,

00:05:50.422 --> 00:05:57.213
in the 15 year case, it
is going to be 180 months;

00:05:57.213 --> 00:05:59.194
and because of that,
your payment for the same

00:05:59.194 --> 00:06:01.964
loan amount is going to
be higher every month

00:06:01.964 --> 00:06:03.737
because you're paying it off quicker.

00:06:03.737 --> 00:06:05.082
You're paying it off in fewer months.

00:06:05.082 --> 00:06:07.698
Instead of $2,000 a month,
maybe it is something

00:06:07.698 --> 00:06:12.602
like $2,800 a month for the 15 year case.

00:06:12.602 --> 00:06:14.791
You're paying it off quicker.

00:06:14.791 --> 00:06:17.641
The 5/1 ARM case, and you'll see,

00:06:17.641 --> 00:06:19.412
and there are many types of ARMs,

00:06:19.412 --> 00:06:20.996
and I'm going to explain to
you in a second what an ARM is,

00:06:20.996 --> 00:06:23.242
but the 5/1 is the most typical.

00:06:23.242 --> 00:06:25.511
I'll explain what that means in a second.

00:06:25.511 --> 00:06:30.312
ARM means 'Adjustable Rate Mortgage.'

00:06:30.312 --> 00:06:34.042
Adjdustable

00:06:34.042 --> 00:06:36.198
Rate

00:06:36.198 --> 00:06:37.928
Mortgage

00:06:37.928 --> 00:06:40.635
As you see, in these situations we had

00:06:40.635 --> 00:06:42.980
the word 'fixed,' and
they were called fixed

00:06:42.980 --> 00:06:45.104
because the interest rate was fixed;

00:06:45.104 --> 00:06:48.282
whatever your remaining
loan balance was you paid

00:06:48.282 --> 00:06:52.545
the same fixed amount of
interest for the next period.

00:06:52.545 --> 00:06:55.927
For this 30 year fixed,
we are being quoted

00:06:55.927 --> 00:06:59.194
a 5% fixed rate over the next
30 years; will not change.

00:06:59.194 --> 00:07:02.764
For the 15 year, we're
quoted a 4% fixed rate.

00:07:02.764 --> 00:07:06.217
For the ARM, the rate can change.

00:07:06.217 --> 00:07:08.993
When someone tells you about a 5/1 ARM,

00:07:08.993 --> 00:07:11.006
they're actually talking about
something called a hybrid ARM;

00:07:11.006 --> 00:07:12.879
but, the general idea behind an adjustable

00:07:12.879 --> 00:07:15.858
rate mortgage is the
amount of interest you pay

00:07:15.858 --> 00:07:17.751
on your remaining balance will change.

00:07:17.751 --> 00:07:19.892
It will change according to some index.

00:07:19.892 --> 00:07:23.131
The most typical types of
adjustable rate mortgages

00:07:23.131 --> 00:07:27.412
are things like this hybrid
ARM; so this is a hybrid.

00:07:27.412 --> 00:07:30.879
A hybrid, it's viewed as
a mixture of 2 things,

00:07:30.879 --> 00:07:33.107
or a combination of 2 things.

00:07:33.107 --> 00:07:35.205
What a hybrid adjustable rate mortgage is

00:07:35.205 --> 00:07:38.167
it has fixed rate for some period of time.

00:07:38.167 --> 00:07:43.576
In this case, it's a
fixed rate for 5 years,

00:07:43.576 --> 00:07:47.008
then the interest rate
can change once a year

00:07:47.008 --> 00:07:50.114
after that, or every 1 years after that.

00:07:50.114 --> 00:07:52.918
That's what this right
over here is telling you.

00:07:52.918 --> 00:07:55.918
In the case of an adjustable rate mortgage

