your payment might look
something like this,

00:07:58.800 --> 00:08:01.286
and I'll just make up
numbers for simplicity

00:08:01.286 --> 00:08:03.432
just to give you the flavor
of what it might look like.

00:08:03.432 --> 00:08:08.448
In the case of a 5/1, your
first 5 years are fixed.

00:08:08.448 --> 00:08:13.585
Your first 5 years. Month 1
is going to look like that.

00:08:13.585 --> 00:08:15.707
Month 2 is going to look like that.

00:08:15.707 --> 00:08:17.551
You go all the way to month 60,

